CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 13, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Honor Tea - Mrs. A Strother Carter of 1507 Boyle Street, gave a tea in honor of her mother Mrs. Eva J. Carson of Oklahoma City, Okla. Mrs. Carson is seated in center with her daughter behind her. Mrs. Samuel J. Spear was guest registrar and Mrs. Martha Barnard received guests.  The honor guest attended the BYPU Congress in Chicago before coming here. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Full length group portrait of women, including Eva J. Carson, guest of honor, seated in center with daughter Mrs. A Strother Carter behind her, Mrs. Samuel J. Spear and Martha Barnard, gathered for tea in Carter home on 1507 Boyle Street, another version
